# UI Standards

- Background: `#0a0a0a` (near-black)
- Accent: amber/gold `#f59e0b` — one accent, used consistently
- Interactive components: four states — idle / loading / ready / active
- Always show loading states
- Mobile-first: stack cards below `768px`
- Use Tailwind `transition` classes between states
- Surface errors on screen, not only in console

## V0 + Cursor workflow

**V0 (v0.dev):** Generate visual UI — cards, buttons, dashboards, landing pages, animations.

**Cursor:** Wire logic — props, API calls, state, TypeScript types, audio recording, API routes, DB.

1. Build UI in v0.dev → copy code → paste into component file in Cursor
2. In Agent chat, specify real props and handlers, e.g.:

```
Connect this V0 component to real data:
- Cards receive props: { counter, grammarian, evaluator } (AI feedback strings)
- Play button onClick → playVoice(text, voiceId)
- Loading when isAnalyzing is true
- Voice IDs: counter=DODLEQrClDo8wCz460ld, grammarian=AeRdCCKzvd23BpJoofzx, evaluator=EST9Ui6982FZPSi7gCHi
Add TypeScript props and wire handlers.
```

| Use V0 first              | Use Cursor directly      |
|---------------------------|--------------------------|
| Cards, buttons, dashboards| API routes               |
| Visual / animated UI      | Supabase queries         |
| Landing / onboarding      | Audio recording logic    |
|                           | Error handling           |

Do not ask Cursor to redesign components V0 already built — integrate only.
